10:
Despite MANY trials and
tribulations... we finally made it to
the last day of the festival!
14:
Just one more day, and we can call
the whole event a success!
17: You've done a good job so far.
21:
From what I heard, we should be
getting a ton of guests from Shibuya
today. I'd already call that a huge
success as is.
26:
Really? Then our last big concern is
making sure the concert goes off
without a hitch—
29:
Er, maybe I shouldn't get ahead of
myself. There's no telling what other
problems might pop up.
32:
We must stand ready to solve any
and all issues that come our way!
37:
I wouldn't be too paranoid about it.
We made it this far without anything
super terrible happening, right?
40:
Luciada! We received a report that
the elemental machinery in the
exhibition building broke down for
some unknown reason!
43: So today's round of trouble begins...
47:
But something like this can be taken
care of easily! I'll go and find a
replacement right away—
51:
Pres! Sha Suzu's new invention
suddenly exploded—
53:
U-um, Luciada, there's a bunch of
Shibuyans in the courtyard—
55: Luciada, we've got a teensy problem—
59:
H-hold on, everyone! Slow down!
One at a time!
67:
Why is there just so much
happening today? Is it because we
have more visitors than usual? Or
are we just suffering from success?
71:
Heh... Hehehehe... Fine. Bring it on. I'll
take on any challenge that comes
my way!
74:
I will make sure this festival is a
success, no matter what! Everything
will be PERFECT—
81: What is it now? Lay it on me!
83:
U-uh... The singer for today's concert
suddenly collapsed from abdominal
pain...
86: It's over. It's all over. We're doomed.
94:
The concert is the main draw of the
festival! Without it, we're nothing!
98:
I was so looking forward to it too! I
LOVE Binary Planet!
100:
We may as well just pack it up and
go home now.
103:
What? Don't look at me like that. If
you can magically summon a
replacement singer from out of
nowhere, then be my guest.
106: O-okay, you know I can't do that—
110: Excuse me! Is my brother here?
113:
Hello, everyone! Thanks for your
hard work. We brought snacks—
119:
The diva herself! Luciada! There's
your replacement singer!
123:
What? Huh? What are you shouting
about, Alk? You're scaring me...
130: N-no, no, no... This is all too sudden!
133:
I haven't practiced or made any of
the proper arrangements! I can't
take on a job that I'm not prepared
for!
137:
Right... I guess as a professional, you
have standards...
141:
But Dia, you already know how to
sing Binary Planet, right?
145: Please, Dia. Won't you do it? For me?
147:
I know I'm being selfish. You have
your pride as a pro, too. But I think
it'd be nice if more people heard
Binary Planet and came to love it.
157:
Binary Planet was discovered on a
vi-deo site, I believe it's called. No
one knows who the original creator
is or how it came to be.
159:
It's a song about two planets, bound
to one another and supporting each
other...
161:
It became well known among the
Shibuyans when it played in their
emergency shelter, serving as a
source of comfort during trying
times.
164:
I think it'd be wonderful if it came to
serve as a symbol of unity between
Shibuyans and Palpebrans as well.
168:
With that in mind, would you
consider lending us your aid?
173:
I want to hear your rendition of
Binary Planet, Dia.
178: Not you too, Stella! That's not fair!
182:
All right. You guys win. I'll perform
Binary Planet for the concert.
192:
Regis, you heard everything, right? I
know you did. I need you to prep
equipment and staff ASAP. Three
hours? No, make it thirty minutes. I
know you can do it.
195:
Also bring the thing that Yuki and I
thought up. You know the one. Yes,
yes, I know I'm being unreasonable.
Now go! Don't be late!
198:
If we're doing this, then we're doing it
right! Let's get to it!
202:
Alk, Stella! Please help Dia with
whatever she needs!
207:
You there! You're in charge of
helping the festival committee for
now. I'm off to make the rounds and
rectify some problems!
213: Is there anything we can help with?
217:
First you bring Dia here, and now
you're offering a hand? Where have
you been all my life?
222:
Hehe, I haven't even really done
anything yet!
225:
Then let's change that. Could you
help me carry some replacement
equipment? We've got technical
problems cropping up all over the
place...
234:
You sure are convenient to have
around, Sho! I can't believe I'm lifting
something this big without breaking
a sweat!
237:
You might not, but I sure am! This is
a lotta work for me!
240:
This cryptic artifact is misbehaving,
you say? I don't see any magical
damage to it. Hm... What a
fascinating defect.
244: Liam? What are you doing here?
249:
Oh? Fancy seeing you again. I'm
here about a strange cryptic
artifact, in fact—
252:
...Do my eyes deceive me? Is that
you, Luciada?
